  "description": {
    "en": "Learn the re module — match, search, findall, and basic patterns like \\d, \\w, \\s, character classes, and quantifiers.",
    "ta": "re module — match, search, findall, மற்றும் \\d, \\w, \\s, character classes, quantifiers போன்ற அடிப்படை patterns கற்றுக்கொள்ளுங்கள்."
  },
  "xp_reward": 65,
  "story_variants": {
    "en": "## Vaathiyaar's Detective Magnifier\n\nVaathiyaar pulls out a magnifying glass. \"Imagine you have a 10,000-line log file and need to find every phone number, email, or IP address. Searching manually? Impossible. Regular expressions are your **pattern-matching superpower**!\"\n\n### The re Module\n\n```python\nimport re\nresult = re.search(r'\\d{3}-\\d{4}', 'Call 555-1234')\nprint(result.group())  # 555-1234\n```\n\n### Pattern Cheat Sheet\n\n| Pattern | Matches | Example |\n|---------|---------|----------|\n| `\\d` | Any digit | `0-9` |\n| `\\w` | Word character | `a-z, A-Z, 0-9, _` |\n| `\\s` | Whitespace | `space, tab, newline` |\n| `.` | Any char (except newline) | anything |\n| `*` | 0 or more | `ab*` → a, ab, abb... |\n| `+` | 1 or more | `ab+` → ab, abb... |\n| `?` | 0 or 1 | `colou?r` → color, colour |\n| `{n}` | Exactly n | `\\d{3}` → 3 digits |\n\n> **Key Concept:** Always use raw strings `r'...'` for regex patterns. This prevents Python from interpreting backslashes before regex sees them."
  },
